Wire the thermistor in a divider with a 10 k metal-film 1 percent resistor:

- 3.3 V -> 10 k (R_top) -> ADC node -> NTC (R_th) -> GND

Read raw, compute R_th = R_top * raw / (4095 - raw) for a 12-bit ADC at 3.3 V.

```cpp
const float R_TOP = 10000.0;
const float R0 = 10000.0;
const float B = 3950.0;
const float T0_K = 298.15;

float readTempC() {
  int raw = analogRead(A0);
  float r = R_TOP * (4095.0 - raw) / raw;  // NTC on bottom: invert
  float invT = 1.0 / T0_K + log(r / R0) / B;
  return 1.0 / invT - 273.15;
}
```

Add a 100 nF cap from the ADC node to GND, average 16 reads. Place the NTC away from self-heating sources. For accuracy beyond +/-1 C use a Steinhart-Hart 3-term fit or a calibrated polynomial.

```cpp
#include <Wire.h>
#include <Adafruit_INA219.h>

Adafruit_INA219 ina;

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);
  Wire.begin();
  if (!ina.begin()) { while (true) {} }
  // Default config: 32 V bus, 3.2 A range, 800 us conversion, +/-1 mA resolution
  // For sub-mA use ina.setCalibration_16V_400mA();
}

void loop() {
  Serial.print(ina.getBusVoltage_V(), 3);
